const faqJsonLd = {"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "How much does RunPod cost per month for a small OSS LLM workload?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "If you deploy a Llama 3.1 8B endpoint on an RTX 4090 ($0.69/hr) via Serverless and serve ~5K requests/day with 2-second average latency, your bill is roughly $4-8/month plus idle cost. A dedicated H100 pod for fine-tuning (12 hours x $2.89/hr ~ $35) is a one-time cost per training run. The $5 starter credit covers 1-3 small pods end-to-end."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Is RunPod usable from China?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Partially. RunPod's primary regions are US (us-east, us-west), EU (eu-west), and AU/Asia (ap-southeast, ap-northeast). Direct access from mainland China is unstable -- most teams use a stable proxy or route through Aliyun's international gateway. Some users report 200-400ms additional latency versus Modal/Baseten on the same routes."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Does RunPod charge for idle GPU time?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "No -- that's the central cost advantage. Serverless endpoints scale to zero when idle (only pay for active workers). Pods bill by the second while running, and only while running -- you can stop and start them. This is different from AWS/GCP where an idle EC2 instance still bills. For spiky workloads (text-image generation, batch jobs), RunPod is 3-10x cheaper than keeping an A100 warm on AWS."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How does RunPod compare to Modal or Baseten?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Modal has the best Python developer experience ($30/mo free, scale to zero, sub-second cold starts) but charges for container runtime regardless of idle. Baseten offers dedicated deployments with SLA plus Truss for custom models. RunPod wins on raw price-per-GPU-second and GPU catalog breadth (13+ tiers from RTX 4090 to B300)